commit.message: Support imports with underscores and numbers
Support syntax from X import Y
Fix failures when module is imported with an alias, for example: if you use to import numpy, then search for will fail. I added a function to replace aliases with there true name.

Add lowercase command abbreviations

Lowercase command abbreviations allow for quicker use.
With this change, it is possible to type `:pyd<space>`
to bring up the view, or `pyds<space>` to search.

Merge pull request #25 from blueyed/master

Drop `silent` prefixes

Drop `silent` prefixes

The silent prefix might prevent any output from autocommands, and it
should be unnecessary.

At least it should be avoided for:

    silent execute g:pydoc_open_cmd '__doc__'

Ref: https://github.com/embear/vim-localvimrc/pull/13
